WEBVTT

00:31.682 --> 00:34.250
[ clearing throat]:
For my next trick

00:34.381 --> 00:37.036
notice I have
nothing up my sleeves

00:37.167 --> 00:40.039
and nothing in my head.

00:42.259 --> 00:45.523
So, if my lovely assistant
will kindly supply me

00:45.654 --> 00:49.091
with an ordinary,
non-fake pitcher of milk...

00:51.963 --> 00:54.271
Behold-- the milk has vanished.

00:54.402 --> 00:57.186
Exiled, perhaps,
to another dimension.

00:59.058 --> 01:00.103
Amazing.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.365
That's why they call you
Bender the Magnificent.

01:02.496 --> 01:03.192
No, it isn't.

01:05.194 --> 01:06.283
Whoa.

01:06.414 --> 01:09.938
They discovered an intact
20th-century pizzeria

01:10.069 --> 01:11.418
just like the one
I used to work at.

01:11.549 --> 01:12.855
Interesting.

01:12.984 --> 01:14.161
No, wait,
the other thing.

01:14.290 --> 01:15.162
Tedious.

01:15.292 --> 01:16.206
Let's go
check it out.

01:16.337 --> 01:18.251
You can see how I lived
before I met you.

01:18.382 --> 01:20.036
You lived
before you met me?

01:20.167 --> 01:21.819
Sure, lots of people did.

01:21.950 --> 01:23.299
Really?

01:29.088 --> 01:33.093
[ Bender humming]

01:34.615 --> 01:38.097
Truly, they were as gods,
who built this place.

01:38.228 --> 01:39.272
WOMAN:
Next...

01:39.402 --> 01:40.534
we come

01:40.664 --> 01:43.319
to the splendidly preserved
wooden pizza paddle.

01:43.450 --> 01:44.843
[ beeps]

01:44.973 --> 01:46.975
Scientists theorize

01:47.106 --> 01:49.674
it was used to gently
discipline the delivery boy.

01:53.112 --> 01:54.069
FRY:
Wait a second.

01:54.200 --> 01:55.245
This is Panucci's.

01:55.376 --> 01:57.855
I used to work in
this exact pizzeria.

01:57.986 --> 01:59.640
And for your information, lady

01:59.771 --> 02:02.338
this was not
just used to paddle my butt.

02:02.469 --> 02:04.210
It was also used to move pizzas
and crush rats.

02:04.340 --> 02:06.864
I don't know where
you get your facts, sir

02:06.995 --> 02:11.260
but I am a volunteer housewife
with 45 minutes of orientation

02:11.391 --> 02:14.481
and a Harlequin romance
about archaeologists.

02:14.611 --> 02:16.875
Don't wave
your fancy degrees at me.

02:17.006 --> 02:18.834
I recognize all this stuff.

02:18.963 --> 02:20.704
Petrified sausages

02:20.836 --> 02:22.098
old Mr. Vitelli

02:22.228 --> 02:23.621
and that's...
[ gasping]

02:27.799 --> 02:28.670
[ buzzer]

02:28.800 --> 02:30.150
MAN:
Yes?

02:30.280 --> 02:32.848
Pizza delivery for a Mr...

02:32.978 --> 02:34.022
Seymour Asses.

02:34.153 --> 02:36.199
There's no one
by that name here.

02:36.329 --> 02:37.853
Or anywhere.

02:37.983 --> 02:39.246
I hope that in time

02:39.376 --> 02:41.073
you'll realize
what an idiot you've been.

02:41.204 --> 02:42.639
I wouldn't count on that.

02:45.513 --> 02:46.861
[ whimpering]

02:48.515 --> 02:50.170
Aw. Poor little guy.

02:50.300 --> 02:51.823
You look like

02:51.954 --> 02:53.302
you haven't eaten in a month.

02:53.433 --> 02:54.435
Here.

02:54.564 --> 02:57.437
But if Mr. Panucci asks,
your name is Seymour Asses.

02:57.567 --> 02:58.917
[ barks]

03:00.049 --> 03:01.050
I like you, Seymour.

03:01.181 --> 03:02.530
You're not
constantly judging me

03:02.659 --> 03:04.270
like all the other dogs.

03:04.401 --> 03:05.532
Are you?

03:06.751 --> 03:07.664
Nah.

03:07.795 --> 03:09.145
We understand each other.

03:09.276 --> 03:10.233
[ gobbling]

03:10.364 --> 03:12.843
People think you're just
a dumb mutt who smells bad

03:12.974 --> 03:15.324
can't find a girlfriend
and has a crummy job.

03:15.455 --> 03:18.502
But you're keeping it real
and you call no man "mister."

03:20.503 --> 03:21.635
Well, good-bye.

03:21.765 --> 03:23.681
Live long and prosper.

03:23.812 --> 03:25.421
[ whines softly]

03:29.121 --> 03:31.122
[ barking]

03:31.253 --> 03:33.212
Blech.

03:33.343 --> 03:36.432
That's the least appetizing
calzone I've ever seen.

03:36.563 --> 03:38.218
No, that's my dog
in there.

03:38.348 --> 03:39.914
It's an outrage,
I say.

03:41.350 --> 03:42.352
Hey...

03:42.483 --> 03:43.353
Ow.

03:43.484 --> 03:44.701
I'm taking him home

03:44.832 --> 03:46.094
and I'd like to see anyone

03:46.225 --> 03:47.227
try and stop me. Uh-oh.

03:47.356 --> 03:48.793
[ grunting]

03:52.231 --> 03:54.756
And then he was ejected
by the guards.

03:54.885 --> 03:57.192
Needless to say,
I was mortified.

03:57.324 --> 03:59.543
Well, it's not right to make
my dead pet an exhibit.

03:59.674 --> 04:01.022
That's like
digging up Lassie

04:01.152 --> 04:02.937
and putting her
on display in the Louvre.

04:03.068 --> 04:04.808
Lassie ison display
in the Louvre.

04:04.939 --> 04:05.896
I know.

04:06.027 --> 04:07.289
I was deliberately
describing

04:07.420 --> 04:08.509
a similar situation.

04:08.639 --> 04:10.379
Why don't you try
protesting?

04:10.510 --> 04:12.338
Like those
native Martians.

04:12.468 --> 04:13.600
Always whining that people

04:13.730 --> 04:16.386
don't treat their ancestors
bones with respect.

04:16.516 --> 04:17.692
[ slurping]

04:17.822 --> 04:19.824
Eh, protesting never works.

04:19.954 --> 04:20.824
You're right.

04:20.956 --> 04:22.262
I'll give it a shot.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.177
GROUP:
What do you want?!

04:25.307 --> 04:26.266
Fry's dog!

04:26.396 --> 04:27.831
When do you want it?!

04:27.963 --> 04:29.007
Fry's dog!

04:29.137 --> 04:30.531
[ cheering]

04:30.661 --> 04:33.360
I will now perform
my people's native dance.

04:33.490 --> 04:35.709
[ "The Hustle" plays]

04:35.840 --> 04:37.798
♪ Do the Hustle...

04:42.281 --> 04:43.718
It says here
that this part

04:43.848 --> 04:45.023
of the Hustle

04:45.153 --> 04:46.850
implores the gods
to grant a favor

04:46.981 --> 04:48.288
usually a Trans Am.

04:51.942 --> 04:54.946
♪ I'm walking on sunshine,
oh-oh... ♪

04:55.076 --> 04:57.427
[ barks melody]

04:59.863 --> 05:03.519
♪ I'm walking on sunshine,
whoa-oh... ♪

05:03.651 --> 05:04.869
That-a-boy, Seymour.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.088
Right here waiting
for me as always.

05:07.218 --> 05:09.091
Just like that huge
mushroom in my shower.

05:13.225 --> 05:15.271
Hey, there's our
little mascot.

05:16.533 --> 05:18.970
Aw, you've been swimming
in the sewer again?

05:19.100 --> 05:20.014
You rascal.

05:24.454 --> 05:25.411
Fry, clean up.

05:25.542 --> 05:26.978
Seymour, clean up.

05:28.762 --> 05:30.024
Good dog.

05:30.154 --> 05:31.548
That's a good Seymour.

05:34.420 --> 05:36.771
Yo, there's dog fur
on my slice.

05:36.901 --> 05:38.380
Nah, that's vermicelli.

05:38.512 --> 05:39.687
No fur in here.

05:39.817 --> 05:41.427
[ sneezes]

05:43.691 --> 05:46.649
[ barking]

05:46.781 --> 05:48.303
FRY:
He's so cute.

05:48.435 --> 05:49.697
He can do two things
at one time--

05:49.826 --> 05:51.437
Eat and swim.

05:51.567 --> 05:53.353
Ooh, three things.

05:53.483 --> 05:56.399
[ tape deck slows
and distorts "The Hustle"]

05:57.922 --> 05:59.446
Fry, it's been three days.

05:59.576 --> 06:01.795
You can't keep boogying
like this.

06:01.925 --> 06:04.538
You'll come down with a fever
of some sort.

06:04.668 --> 06:05.495
Mr. Fry

06:05.625 --> 06:07.062
I'm Dr. Ben Beeler

06:07.192 --> 06:09.151
the paleontologist who
discovered your dog

06:09.281 --> 06:11.588
or as some call it,
the Beelersaurus.

06:11.718 --> 06:13.067
So do I get Seymour back?

06:13.197 --> 06:14.809
Are you caving
to political pressure?

06:14.939 --> 06:15.939
No. We're sorry

06:16.071 --> 06:17.463
but there's just
too much

06:17.593 --> 06:19.290
that fossil can teach us

06:19.422 --> 06:20.814
about dogs
from your time.

06:20.944 --> 06:22.468
His name was Seymour.

06:22.598 --> 06:24.514
He was once intimate
with the leg

06:24.644 --> 06:26.081
of a wandering
saxophonist.

06:26.211 --> 06:28.430
He had wet dog smell,
even when dry.

06:28.562 --> 06:31.391
And he was not above chasing
the Number 29 bus.

06:31.521 --> 06:33.088
The 29... interesting.

06:33.218 --> 06:34.394
That's all I needed.
Ray?

06:34.524 --> 06:35.612
I'm good.

06:35.742 --> 06:38.093
Okay, then-- here's
your dog back.

06:38.223 --> 06:39.485
[ chortling]

06:39.615 --> 06:40.399
Seymour!

06:43.620 --> 06:45.055
Lady and gentleman

06:45.187 --> 06:48.973
how about a hand for my
temporary replacement assistant!

06:52.629 --> 06:53.761
I was all in this part.

06:53.891 --> 06:55.110
It's magic.

06:55.240 --> 06:58.983
You're! Not! Fit! To wear!
Fry's! Leotard!

06:59.113 --> 07:00.550
Stop!

07:00.680 --> 07:02.204
Good news, everyone.

07:02.334 --> 07:03.466
Hooray, he's back!

07:03.596 --> 07:04.728
And he's looking

07:04.858 --> 07:06.512
for a garbage can
to put the rock in.

07:06.642 --> 07:07.644
Here you go, buddy.

07:07.774 --> 07:09.646
No, actually we've discovered

07:09.776 --> 07:12.127
that Fry's dog
was fast-fossilized

07:12.257 --> 07:13.954
preserving its cellular
structure.

07:14.084 --> 07:16.348
Which means we can clone it.

07:16.478 --> 07:17.959
Seymour will live again!

07:18.088 --> 07:20.351
A little land mammal.

07:20.483 --> 07:21.963
Can you believe it, Bender?

07:22.093 --> 07:24.399
I'm going to have
my best friend back.

07:26.706 --> 07:29.971
[ sobbing]

07:42.678 --> 07:44.637
Why the idiot
convention?

07:44.768 --> 07:47.379
Ah, Cubert, my precious babe.

07:47.509 --> 07:49.990
I'm going to attempt
to clone Fry's dog

07:50.120 --> 07:53.473
using the very same apparatus
I used to clone you.

07:53.603 --> 07:55.038
Ooh, look.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.519
There's a smidge
of toe still in here.

07:59.435 --> 08:03.394
You see, beneath the fossil's
crunchy mineral shell

08:03.526 --> 08:06.572
there's still a creamy core
of dog nougat.

08:06.702 --> 08:08.704
So will Seymour remember
how to sing

08:08.836 --> 08:09.750
"Walking on Sunshine"?

08:09.879 --> 08:11.752
Amazingly, yes.

08:11.882 --> 08:13.841
In cases of rapid
fossilization

08:13.971 --> 08:16.278
I can press
this brain-scan button

08:16.408 --> 08:18.192
retrieving Seymour's memories

08:18.322 --> 08:20.586
at the precise instant
of doggy death.

08:20.716 --> 08:22.283
I'm going to get my puppy back.

08:22.413 --> 08:24.199
In your face, Grim Reaper!

08:24.329 --> 08:26.288
Crappy, ineffective reaper.

08:26.418 --> 08:29.725
I just need to reset
the Clone-o-Mat from human mode

08:29.856 --> 08:31.074
to dog mode.

08:32.467 --> 08:34.730
COMPUTER VOICE:
The dog says... [ cow moos]

08:34.861 --> 08:37.428
Oh-oh, this may take a while.

08:43.957 --> 08:46.655
You stink, loser!

08:46.787 --> 08:48.831
Hey, Fry,
pizza going out.

08:48.962 --> 08:50.442
Come on!

08:50.572 --> 08:52.532
But I'm celebrating
New Year's Eve.

08:52.662 --> 08:54.750
Like you got squat
to celebrate.

08:54.881 --> 08:56.753
You're a delivery boy
this millennium

08:56.884 --> 08:59.277
and you'll be a delivery boy
next millennium.

08:59.408 --> 09:01.018
[ Fry sighs]

09:02.629 --> 09:04.195
[ whimpering]

09:04.326 --> 09:05.283
What's with Seymour?

09:05.413 --> 09:06.546
It's like he don't want
you to go

09:06.676 --> 09:08.982
or he thinks your pants
is too short or something

09:09.113 --> 09:11.506
which is crazy,
because frankly,
you look fabulous.

09:11.638 --> 09:12.812
Now get going!

09:14.553 --> 09:15.597
[ whining]

09:15.729 --> 09:17.557
I won't be gone long, Seymour.

09:17.687 --> 09:19.341
Just wait here
till I come back.

09:22.344 --> 09:24.912
[ whining]

09:31.004 --> 09:34.442
Hello, pizza delivery for...

09:36.576 --> 09:38.011
Aw, crud.

09:40.884 --> 09:43.799
Here's to another
lousy millennium.

09:45.366 --> 09:47.760
CROWD:
Five... four...

09:47.890 --> 09:49.806
three... two...

09:53.809 --> 09:54.549
[ screams]

09:56.943 --> 09:57.596
What the...?

09:57.726 --> 09:58.597
[ panting]

10:04.298 --> 10:05.778
A dog collar for me?

10:05.908 --> 10:07.128
You shouldn't have.

10:07.258 --> 10:08.129
That's for Seymour.

10:08.259 --> 10:10.566
Oh.

10:10.697 --> 10:12.350
[ squeaking]

10:12.480 --> 10:14.875
Say, why'd you get me
a subscription
to the Daily Growl?

10:15.004 --> 10:17.094
That's not a reputable
journal of opinion.

10:17.225 --> 10:18.618
Oh, that's also
for Seymour.

10:18.748 --> 10:20.793
I'm getting everything
ready for when he's cloned.

10:20.923 --> 10:21.924
Are you on the junk, Fry?

10:22.056 --> 10:23.404
Why are you wasting time

10:23.534 --> 10:25.145
on a creature
of inferior intelligence?

10:25.275 --> 10:26.147
Hey, he was smart.

10:26.277 --> 10:27.148
He could fetch.

10:27.278 --> 10:28.365
I can fetch.

10:32.719 --> 10:33.980
He could dig up bones.

10:34.110 --> 10:35.895
Hello. Charlemagne?

10:38.115 --> 10:40.769
Plus, I bet he couldn't create
a laser show with his head.

10:40.900 --> 10:44.860
[ techno music playing]

10:44.991 --> 10:47.384
Look, Bender,
this has nothing to do with you.

10:47.515 --> 10:48.648
That's impossible!

10:48.778 --> 10:49.865
Now, if you'll excuse me

10:49.996 --> 10:51.868
I'm working
on Seymour's doghouse.

10:53.522 --> 10:55.306
[ grumbling]

10:55.437 --> 10:57.787
No one ever asks if Bender
would like to live

10:57.918 --> 10:59.354
in a tiny little house.

10:59.484 --> 11:00.876
Not that I would.

11:01.008 --> 11:03.357
A tiny little house
that says "Bender" on it.

11:05.142 --> 11:06.708
Ow!

11:09.885 --> 11:11.322
This is Fry.

11:11.452 --> 11:12.932
If you're calling
about the used towels for sale

11:13.062 --> 11:15.152
they're still available
for $45 each.

11:15.283 --> 11:16.763
[ answering machine beeping]

11:16.893 --> 11:17.677
Phil, it's your father.

11:17.807 --> 11:18.894
Where are you?

11:19.025 --> 11:20.809
You're holding up New Years
brunch.

11:20.941 --> 11:22.682
Your brother can't wait
any longer.

11:22.812 --> 11:26.033
Hello, first bologna
of the new millennium.

11:26.163 --> 11:27.687
[ Seymour barking]

11:27.817 --> 11:28.904
Ah, here he comes.

11:29.036 --> 11:30.384
That's him and Seymour.

11:32.865 --> 11:33.692
Well, that's weird.

11:33.822 --> 11:34.736
Seymour's here, but...

11:34.868 --> 11:38.131
Go! Go! Touchdown!

11:38.261 --> 11:39.437
But where's Philip?

11:39.567 --> 11:42.135
I'm telling you,
the Y2K computer's got him.

11:42.265 --> 11:45.879
We'll face burning roads,
rivers exploding

11:46.009 --> 11:48.794
calculators transformed
into Scud missiles.

11:48.924 --> 11:50.840
There's nothing we can do.

11:51.971 --> 11:55.845
[ barks "Walking On Sunshine"]

11:55.975 --> 11:56.846
What's that,
Seymour?

11:56.976 --> 11:58.804
You walking on sunshine?

11:59.806 --> 12:01.850
[ whining]

12:01.981 --> 12:03.374
He's trying to tell us
something.

12:03.504 --> 12:04.811
Maybe he can lead us
to Philip.

12:05.855 --> 12:07.378
Should we
follow him?

12:07.509 --> 12:09.816
To our deaths?
Negatory.

12:09.946 --> 12:11.947
It's the Y2K trying
to lure us

12:12.078 --> 12:14.168
into an ambush,
and I ain't buying it.

12:14.298 --> 12:15.604
Pass the bologna.

12:23.611 --> 12:26.745
[ karate yells]

12:26.875 --> 12:28.225
Are you two going
to be done soon?

12:28.355 --> 12:31.053
Sorry, but we need to practice
hand-to-hand combat

12:31.184 --> 12:33.274
in case an enemy knocks
the laser guns

12:33.403 --> 12:36.058
out of our hands and they slide
way across the room.

12:36.190 --> 12:37.931
Well, could you do it
someplace else?

12:38.061 --> 12:39.540
I'm setting up Seymour's
doggie bed.

12:39.671 --> 12:40.933
Okay.

12:41.063 --> 12:41.977
Ow!

12:44.240 --> 12:46.025
[ whistling tune]

12:47.941 --> 12:48.985
Heel, boy, heel.

12:49.115 --> 12:49.769
Oh, hello, Fry.

12:49.899 --> 12:52.075
I guess I didn't
notice you there.

12:52.206 --> 12:55.034
I'm having such fun
with my new best friend

12:55.164 --> 12:56.297
Robo-Puppy.

12:56.427 --> 12:57.732
That's nice.

12:57.864 --> 12:59.299
I was just out walking him.

12:59.429 --> 13:00.866
Yes, you can walk him.

13:00.996 --> 13:02.129
Of course, after he goes

13:02.259 --> 13:04.086
you have to refill
the canisters.

13:04.217 --> 13:06.916
Come here, boy.
Pet. Pet. Pet.

13:07.047 --> 13:08.700
Robo-Puppy receiving petting.

13:08.831 --> 13:11.528
Bender, are
you jealous
of Fry's puppy?

13:11.659 --> 13:13.313
That's so adorable.

13:13.443 --> 13:17.797
Jealous? Not when I have
the love of Robo-Puppy here.

13:17.927 --> 13:19.798
Robo-Puppy, lick my cheek.

13:19.928 --> 13:23.366
Robo-Puppy preparing
to lick cheek.

13:23.498 --> 13:26.326
Robo-Puppy commencing
cheek licking.

13:26.456 --> 13:27.850
Licking in progress.

13:27.980 --> 13:29.677
Licking complete.

13:29.808 --> 13:32.942
Robo-Puppy truly is
robot's best friend, huh?

13:33.072 --> 13:34.596
There, perfect.

13:34.725 --> 13:36.859
[ fanfare playing]

13:36.990 --> 13:38.860
Good news, everyone.

13:38.991 --> 13:41.558
The Clone-o-Mat is ready!

13:41.690 --> 13:42.822
[ cheering]

13:44.126 --> 13:45.040
Finally.

13:45.172 --> 13:46.173
[ growls]

13:46.302 --> 13:50.264
Robo-Puppy commencing
two hour yipping session.

13:50.394 --> 13:52.134
[ mechanical yipping]

13:52.265 --> 13:53.919
Shut up.

13:55.051 --> 13:57.096
Robo-Puppy mistreatment alert!

13:57.226 --> 13:59.273
Robo-Puppy
mistreatment alert!

14:01.404 --> 14:05.495
Behold once more,
the mighty Clone-o-Mat.

14:05.626 --> 14:09.065
Requiring such vast amounts
of electricity that we must

14:09.196 --> 14:13.721
harness the elemental power
of nature itself.

14:13.852 --> 14:15.071
[ thunder crashing][ all gasping]

14:15.201 --> 14:17.029
I speak, of course

14:17.159 --> 14:20.903
of molten lava deep within
the Earth's core.

14:21.033 --> 14:23.036
To the subbasement.

14:23.166 --> 14:25.865
[ clanking]

14:25.995 --> 14:28.562
[ grunting]

14:32.871 --> 14:34.350
[ all gasping]

14:36.875 --> 14:39.095
Powering up Clone-o-Mat.

14:41.315 --> 14:45.580
Placing fossil on the
plat-clone-o-form.

14:45.710 --> 14:47.015
[ electrical crackling]

14:47.147 --> 14:49.889
Initiating dog brain CAT scan.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.676
Come on, boy,
come back to life.

14:54.806 --> 14:59.462
Know ye now what it feels like
to be Dog God.

14:59.594 --> 15:03.815
Commencing DNA extraction.

15:03.946 --> 15:05.991
[ high-pitched whirring]

15:06.121 --> 15:07.818
[ all gasping]

15:09.038 --> 15:10.822
Fry, come on

15:10.952 --> 15:12.562
the talent show.

15:12.693 --> 15:14.000
What? I'm in the middle
of something.

15:14.129 --> 15:17.917
But if we don't perform,
in what sense do we have an act?

15:18.047 --> 15:20.005
Bender, enough.
Leave me alone.

15:20.135 --> 15:22.572
So that's how it is, huh?

15:22.703 --> 15:24.139
I thought you were my friend

15:24.270 --> 15:26.837
but if you love
your dog so much

15:26.969 --> 15:28.623
maybe you'd rather play fetch.

15:31.278 --> 15:32.844
No!
Oh!
No!

15:34.933 --> 15:36.065
[ screams]

15:36.196 --> 15:38.024
[ evil cackle]

15:38.153 --> 15:40.940
Now I'm all you got.

15:45.248 --> 15:47.293
I hate you!
[ clanking]

15:47.423 --> 15:50.123
I hate you, you
evil metal man!

15:50.253 --> 15:51.951
Ow!

15:52.081 --> 15:53.474
So anyway, your dog
is melted.

15:53.604 --> 15:54.953
Now we're friends again.

15:55.084 --> 15:55.955
Not necessarily.

15:56.085 --> 15:58.173
For the dog may yet survive.

15:58.304 --> 15:59.914
May yet? Really?

16:00.046 --> 16:01.003
Indeed.

16:01.134 --> 16:03.831
You see, that fossil
was made of dolomite--

16:03.962 --> 16:06.312
the tough black mineral
that won't cop out

16:06.442 --> 16:08.053
when there's heat all about.

16:08.183 --> 16:11.013
By contrast, observe
the lava's effect

16:11.144 --> 16:13.754
on this ice swan.

16:16.192 --> 16:17.759
Of course, that would
have melted

16:17.889 --> 16:18.977
even at room temperature.

16:19.107 --> 16:20.849
I just wanted
to get rid of it.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.982
But had it been made of that
righteous mineral dolomite

16:24.113 --> 16:26.462
there's a slim chance
it might have survived.

16:26.594 --> 16:28.465
So Seymour might
still exist?

16:28.596 --> 16:30.466
Perhaps, for
a few minutes.

16:30.597 --> 16:32.033
It's dolomite, baby.

16:32.164 --> 16:35.298
Then I'm going in after him.

16:35.428 --> 16:37.256
[ grunting]

16:37.386 --> 16:38.475
[ all hollering]

16:38.605 --> 16:41.216
He'd come after me.

16:42.261 --> 16:45.004
[ barking]

17:04.109 --> 17:05.675
[ whimpers]

17:08.330 --> 17:10.376
[ panting]

17:10.507 --> 17:12.682
[ sniffing]

17:17.471 --> 17:19.125
[ barking]

17:25.260 --> 17:28.047
Acting like a moron
won't bring your dog back.

17:28.176 --> 17:29.178
Then all hope
is lost.

17:29.308 --> 17:32.224
[ sniffling]

17:32.355 --> 17:34.182
Good-bye, Seymour.

17:34.314 --> 17:35.792
[ sobbing]

17:35.923 --> 17:39.144
Please stop
crying, Fry.

17:39.275 --> 17:40.842
Here.

17:40.971 --> 17:43.365
I assumed you
were just
pretending

17:43.497 --> 17:44.585
to love the dog

17:44.714 --> 17:46.413
to toy with
my emotions.

17:46.542 --> 17:49.023
Oh, what have I done?!

17:49.154 --> 17:50.373
You didn't do anything.

17:50.503 --> 17:51.982
Don't beat yourself up.

17:52.114 --> 17:53.288
Fry, I'm sorry.

17:53.420 --> 17:56.204
I should have understood
how someone can love

17:56.336 --> 17:59.295
an inferior creature,
because I love you.

17:59.425 --> 18:01.557
Not in the way
of the ancient Greeks

18:01.689 --> 18:03.951
but the way a robot
loves a human--

18:04.083 --> 18:05.084
a human loves a dog--

18:05.213 --> 18:08.042
and occasionally
a gorilla loves a kitty.

18:08.173 --> 18:09.784
I'm going in.

18:09.913 --> 18:11.176
I'm a professor.

18:11.307 --> 18:13.614
Why isn't anyone
listening to me?

18:13.743 --> 18:15.528
You can't go in
because you'll melt.

18:15.659 --> 18:18.792
The fossil only has a chance
because it's made of dolomite.

18:18.923 --> 18:21.403
I'm 40% dolomite.

18:24.277 --> 18:25.146
[ all gasping]

18:25.278 --> 18:27.236
Oh, it's hot.
Oh, it's very hot.

18:27.366 --> 18:28.541
[ clanking]

18:33.373 --> 18:35.548
[ barking]

18:37.463 --> 18:41.119
Oh, I am one hung-over
cryogenicist.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.772
Just throw that mutt
in the freezer

18:42.903 --> 18:44.297
till his owners get here.

18:44.426 --> 18:46.385
You can't solve all your
problems by freezing them, boss.

18:46.516 --> 18:48.605
I think you're forgetting
our motto.

18:51.826 --> 18:55.612
Are you the cryogenicist
who called about our son's dog?

18:55.742 --> 18:57.353
You must
be the Frys.

18:57.483 --> 18:59.876
Yeah, he's
right over there.

19:00.008 --> 19:01.269
Sorry we're late.

19:01.401 --> 19:03.142
We all got sick
from eating
bad balogna.

19:03.271 --> 19:04.490
Y2K.

19:06.840 --> 19:08.451
What's he so
worked up about?

19:08.582 --> 19:12.019
He's just upset 'cause
our boy's missing.

19:12.151 --> 19:14.240
Come on, you overgrown rat,
lead us to Philip.

19:14.369 --> 19:17.807
[ whimpering]

19:21.724 --> 19:23.162
Bender's been
down there
too long.

19:23.291 --> 19:24.292
I'm going in
after him.

19:24.423 --> 19:26.861
Professor! Lava! Hot!

19:26.990 --> 19:28.297
This is all my fault.

19:28.428 --> 19:30.691
I let my best friend
risk his life

19:30.820 --> 19:32.736
just to get my dead dog back.

19:32.866 --> 19:34.607
[ sobbing]

19:35.826 --> 19:38.046
[ rumbling]

19:40.048 --> 19:40.743
Bender!

19:40.875 --> 19:42.310
And that is why

19:42.442 --> 19:45.401
they call me
Bender the magnificent.

19:45.531 --> 19:48.143
Hey, where'd everybody go?

19:51.319 --> 19:53.365
Okay, let's clone us some dog.

19:53.496 --> 19:54.148
Yeah!

19:54.279 --> 19:55.628
Very well--

19:55.759 --> 19:59.109
let this abomination
unto the Lord begin!

19:59.240 --> 20:01.155
[ high-pitched whirring]

20:03.506 --> 20:05.464
Interesting.

20:05.595 --> 20:09.685
It seems Seymour died
at the ripe old age of 15.

20:09.817 --> 20:10.773
Fifteen?

20:10.904 --> 20:12.515
You mean, he lived
for 12 more years

20:12.645 --> 20:13.516
after I got frozen?

20:13.646 --> 20:14.734
Indeed.

20:14.865 --> 20:16.563
Stop the cloning.

20:16.692 --> 20:17.346
[ both gasp]

20:19.869 --> 20:23.439
Oh, sure,
smash the smart guy's machine.

20:23.569 --> 20:24.440
Fry, what's wrong?

20:24.570 --> 20:25.571
Think about it.

20:25.701 --> 20:27.790
Seymour lived a full life
after I was gone.

20:27.922 --> 20:30.794
He probably even added
new songs to his repertoire...

20:30.924 --> 20:32.361
But that's a good thing.

20:32.491 --> 20:34.493
"Walking on Sunshine"
sucks noodles.

20:34.624 --> 20:36.451
I had Seymour till
he was three.

20:36.583 --> 20:39.367
That's when I knew him,
and that's when I loved him.

20:40.673 --> 20:43.023
I'll never forget him...

20:43.153 --> 20:46.593
but he forgot me
a long, long time ago.

20:54.775 --> 21:01.477
♪ If it takes forever

21:01.607 --> 21:07.482
♪ I will wait for you

21:07.614 --> 21:12.140
♪ For a thousand summers

21:12.270 --> 21:16.839
♪ I will wait for you

21:16.971 --> 21:21.279
♪ Till you're back beside me

21:21.410 --> 21:26.196
♪ Till I'm holding you

21:26.327 --> 21:29.809
♪ Till I hear you sigh

21:29.940 --> 21:32.290
♪ Here in my arms...

21:32.421 --> 21:33.552
Ow!

21:35.423 --> 21:40.429
♪ If it takes forever

21:40.559 --> 21:46.957
♪ I will wait for you

21:47.087 --> 21:49.394
♪ For a thousand summers

21:49.525 --> 21:54.964
♪ I will wait for you...
